cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.DL, cs.IR 

This paper belongs to the computer science sub-category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) as it focuses on investigating illicit activities on the deep and dark web. Additionally, the use of LDA and non-parametric HMM for topic modeling and identifying anomalous events suggests a focus on machine learning and data analysis (cs.SI, cs.DL). The study of the d2web also involves issues of privacy and encryption (cs.CY) and information retrieval (cs.IR) as the authors analyze a large corpus of messages posted to multiple forums.
